Package: coreMicrobiome
Title: Core microbiome analysis and visualization
Version: 2.0
Authors@R: person("Dan", "LIN", , "dlinlin.1128@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: coreMicrobiome is a R package for scientists to conduct explore and visualization of core microbial species which comprises four functional modules: (1) Initial visualization of sampling effort and distribution of dominant bacterial taxa among groups or individual samples at different taxonomic levels; (2) Analysis of Abundance-occupancy distribution and visualizations; (3) Co-occurrence network construction, analysis, comparisons and visualizations; (4) A combined visualization of abundance-occupancy distribution and co-occurrence network for understanding the core species from the common perspective and ecosystem perspective.
Depends: R
Imports: dplyr, tidyr
Suggests: phyloseq, microbiome, ggplot2, plotly, ggpubr, gridExtra, ggtree, UpSet, pheatmap, vegan, tidygraph, reshape2, ape, randomForest, caret, propr, compositions, igraph, qgraph, ggraph, ComplexHeatmap, circlize, mixOmics
License: `use_mit_license()`, `use_gpl3_license()` or friends to pick a license
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.1.2
